Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly spray cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, combine quick bread mix and swirl mix from packet; mix well. Add oil, 2 tablespoons coffee and egg; blend well. Add chips; mix well. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls; place on sprayed cookie sheets. Flatten balls to 1/2-inch thickness. Bake at 350 degrees F for 9 to 14 minutes or until edges are set and light golden brown. Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheets; place on wire rack. Cool 10 minutes. In small bowl, combine glaze from packet and 1 teaspoon coffee; blend until smooth. Drizzle glaze over cookies.